&= \frac{1}{\frac{(x+3)+(x+2)}{(x+2)(x+3)}} \\
&= \frac{1}{\frac{2 x+5}{(x+2)(x+3)}}
\end{align*}
\]
Now, we can take the reciprocal of both sides to get:
\[
\begin{align*}
\frac{(x+2)(x+3)}{2 x+5} &= \frac{(x+2)(x+3)}{1} \cdot \frac{1}{2x+5} \\
&= \frac{x^2 + 5x + 6}{2x + 5}
\end{align*}
\]
So, the equivalent expression is $\frac{x^2 + 5x + 6}{2x + 5}$.

